'''polyacid'''
# {{chemistry}} Capable of [[neutralize|neutralizing]], or of combining with, several [[molecule]]s of a [[monobasic]] [[acid]]; having more than one [[hydrogen]] [[atom]] capable of being replaced by [[acid radical]]s; -- said of certain [[base]]s; as, c[[alcium hydrate]] and [[glycerin]] are polyacid bases.

